author: Online
title: Jumbo tops Euro-Med
text:
Games Monday (Filoil Flying V Arena) 4 p.m. – Foton Toplander vs Kama Motors 6 p.m. – Sta. Lucia vs Caida Tiles 
Jumbo Plastic Linoleum relied on its solid defense to ground Euro-Med’s big guns and handed the team its first loss in the tournament after pulling off a 79-65 win in the PCBL Founders Cup at the Filoil Flying V Arena. 
The win enabled Jumbo Plastic to forge a three-way tie for second to fourth places with its rival and idle Sta, Lucia with the same 2-1 win-loss record in this tournament being supported by Spalding, Accel, Aquabest and Ambucore. Caida Tiles continued to hold on to solo lead with a 3-0 record. 
Playing small ball against Euro-Med, Jumbo Plastic neutralized high-scoring Bong Gallanza, who was held to just 10 points on a woeful 2-of-11 shooting from the field. 
With Gallanza grounded, Euro-Med’s production suffered. The team shot below 35% from the field. 
Burly frontliner JR Taganas muscled his way for a double-double performance, tallying 20 points and 14 rebounds while Jeff Biernes contributed 12. Ex-pro Alvin Padilla and John Lopez added 10 apiece.
